Apple’s Pages now allows users to  <a href="https://support.apple.com/en-us/HT207569">add formulas</a> with LaTeX. It’s looking like a good solution for those who like more traditional word processors.
</p></div></div>

 <div class="footdef"> <sup> <a id="fn.2" class="footnum" href="#fnr.2" role="doc-backlink">2</a></sup> <div class="footpara" role="doc-footnote"> <p class="footpara">
